    "created_at": "2014-01-13T12:22:13Z",
    "updated_at": "2014-01-13T12:22:27Z",
    "body": "This (or something equivalent) can be written with [a macro](http://static.rust-lang.org/doc/master/guide-macros.html):\n\n``` rust\n#[feature(macro_rules)];\n\nmacro_rules! bind {\n    ($( $p:pat $(: $t:ty)* = $val:expr );* in $rhs:expr) => {\n        {\n            $( let $p $(: $t)* = $val; )*\n            $rhs\n        }\n    }\n}\n\nfn main() {\n    let v = bind!(a: int = 1; b = 2 in a + b);\n    println!(\"{}\", v);\n}\n```\n\nDoes that appear to cover what you are thinking of?\n",
    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
